WEBVTT

00:20.709 --> 00:23.250
♪Graceful Piano♪

00:23.333 --> 00:25.333
JESSICA:
How things
change in a heartbeat.

00:25.417 --> 00:26.625
My flight to Vienna has
been diverted

00:26.709 --> 00:28.875
due to heaven knows what,

00:28.959 --> 00:30.667
and I find myself
in a provincial airport

00:30.750 --> 00:33.166
in northern England.

00:34.333 --> 00:36.875
As charming as that sounds there
are no hotels,

00:36.959 --> 00:39.875
no restaurants and nowhere to
kill a few hours at the airport.

00:41.834 --> 00:43.000
I'm taking a train to
the nearest civilization

00:43.083 --> 00:45.750
in hope that I
can find coffee and-

00:45.834 --> 00:48.417
STATION GUARD:
Excuse me ma'am
are you ok there?

00:48.500 --> 00:51.125
JESSICA:
Oh hi, uh yes thank you.

00:52.375 --> 00:54.709
There'll be one
along in a minute.

00:58.875 --> 01:00.500
Well ok then.

01:00.583 --> 01:02.750
American, hm?

01:03.458 --> 01:08.208
Yes. Hey, um do you
know if there's a town nearby,

01:08.291 --> 01:10.667
I mean closer
than um, Barston?

01:10.750 --> 01:13.709
Well yes there is, are
you looking for someone or...

01:14.583 --> 01:15.750
My flight got diverted.

01:15.834 --> 01:16.625
I've no idea
when I can get another,

01:16.709 --> 01:18.625
I just know it's
an overnight delay

01:18.709 --> 01:20.750
Oh dear, you'll
be needing a hotel then.

01:20.834 --> 01:22.750
Yeah, surely
there's one closer right?

01:22.834 --> 01:24.542
Yeah. Get on the
next train and take the second

01:24.625 --> 01:27.667
stop, Farmoor.

01:27.750 --> 01:30.458
There are a few B&Bs there,

01:30.542 --> 01:33.208
shall I get you a
pamphlet? Hold on...

01:33.834 --> 01:36.834
[TRAIN CHOOS]

01:37.625 --> 01:39.542
Oh you've
got to be kidding me,

01:39.625 --> 01:41.834
where does
this go, wizard school?

01:46.542 --> 01:49.375
Farmoor, 2 stops!

01:51.291 --> 01:56.208
♪LIVELY ORCHESTRAL SWELL♪

02:16.625 --> 02:19.750
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

02:39.083 --> 02:42.709
JESSICA:
What is it they say, when life
gives you lemons, make lemonade?

02:43.458 --> 02:46.041
Just boarded a steam train to
a town I've ever heard of and...

02:46.500 --> 02:49.333
it's quite exciting.

02:50.500 --> 02:53.291
[LIVELY MUSIC CONTINUES]

03:03.041 --> 03:05.000
[MUSIC FADES]

03:05.083 --> 03:06.709
TRAIN CONDUCTOR:
Next station last stop.

03:06.792 --> 03:10.166
Oh no no no no.
Where on earth am I?

03:22.917 --> 03:28.041
♪QUIRKY MUSIC♪

03:46.083 --> 03:52.000
[QUIRKY MUSIC SWELLS]

04:20.041 --> 04:23.083
[MUSIC SETTLES]

04:24.625 --> 04:27.750
AMBER:
Oh hi! I'm sorry we
are just about to close.

04:28.083 --> 04:30.166
Fellow American?
What are the chances?

04:30.250 --> 04:34.667
I'm Amber, Hi. I haven't heard
an accent from home for ages.

04:34.750 --> 04:36.500
Jessica, Jessica Bailey.

04:36.583 --> 04:38.667
Amber Very nice to
meet you. It' not a problem,

04:38.750 --> 04:42.166
just go ahead
and have a seat and relax.

04:42.959 --> 04:45.917
So what brings
you to our sleepy little town?

04:46.208 --> 04:48.667
Well, it's a little
embarrassing, but um...

04:48.750 --> 04:50.000
I got on the train
from the airport and...I...

04:50.083 --> 04:52.083
Fell asleep right?

04:52.166 --> 04:54.000
Yeah, wow! you've done that?

04:54.083 --> 04:57.375
Yes. It's like a
sedative, I can't go anywhere

04:57.458 --> 04:59.709
on that train
without dozing off!

04:59.792 --> 05:01.625
Well listen, you
are in Knaresborough,

05:01.709 --> 05:04.792
we are twenty something
miles from the airport,

05:05.125 --> 05:07.083
it's a charming
town like something

05:07.166 --> 05:08.125
out of a Charles Dickens novel,

05:08.375 --> 05:11.959
complete with
Dickens characters of course.

05:12.041 --> 05:16.417
Everyone drinks tea or some
espresso type based drink but I

05:16.500 --> 05:18.542
keep a secret
stash of special roast filter

05:18.625 --> 05:21.625
that I drink every
morning, how about I make some?

05:21.959 --> 05:24.583
I mean now I
believe in guardian angels.

05:24.667 --> 05:26.208
[BOTH LAUGH]

05:27.125 --> 05:33.000
♪CHARMING ORCHESTRA♪

05:55.041 --> 05:55.875
[MUSIC FADES]

05:55.959 --> 05:59.083
Wow! I mean that
was some serious pie.

05:59.166 --> 06:01.125
My uncle owns this
place, he bakes them,

06:01.208 --> 06:03.250
they're legendary.

06:03.333 --> 06:06.208
Hey, do you know if
there's any hotels nearby?

06:06.291 --> 06:07.458
I'm kind of stuck.

06:07.542 --> 06:10.083
Oh, well there might be a few
pubs that would have some rooms

06:10.166 --> 06:11.875
but they tend to be quite full.

06:12.375 --> 06:14.083
The main ones
close for winter season.

06:14.166 --> 06:16.875
Oh, that's not good.

06:16.959 --> 06:21.125
No, well let me just go
ask my uncle, he knows everyone.

06:24.709 --> 06:29.625
♪CHARMING ACOUSTICS♪

06:34.667 --> 06:36.625
KATIE:
Daddy, food's ready.

06:36.709 --> 06:39.500
ANDREW:
Okay sweetheart, I'll be there
in a minute, stay back now.

06:39.583 --> 06:41.792
Grandma says that if
you say in a minute then

06:41.875 --> 06:43.542
she's giving yours to the birds.

06:44.959 --> 06:46.625
Don't shoot the messenger!

06:46.709 --> 06:48.000
Okay.

06:48.083 --> 06:51.500
♪CHARMING ORCHESTRA♪

06:53.917 --> 06:55.125
Hold on.

07:00.166 --> 07:01.083
[BOTH EXCLAIM]

07:01.166 --> 07:03.834
SANDRA:
Oh! Oh.

07:04.083 --> 07:04.834
Weren't you expecting us?

07:04.917 --> 07:09.000
Well not on
time. That's a first,

07:09.083 --> 07:10.458
wash your hands.

07:11.208 --> 07:15.709
♪QUIRKY MUSIC♪

07:20.041 --> 07:21.500
[GIGGLES AND SPLASHES]

07:22.083 --> 07:24.709
Goose or turkey?

07:24.792 --> 07:26.125
I thought it was
stew, it smells amazing.

07:26.208 --> 07:29.166
No, for Christmas?

07:29.250 --> 07:30.667
Christmas?

07:30.750 --> 07:31.000
Whatever you like mum.

07:31.083 --> 07:33.208
Katie?

07:33.291 --> 07:35.667
Katie Can we have...
Mince pies for breakfast,

07:35.750 --> 07:37.542
Turkey and roast
potatoes for lunch

07:37.625 --> 07:39.083
and chocolate
trifle for dinner?

07:39.166 --> 07:42.917
Oh well that's
a nice try poppet.

07:43.000 --> 07:45.208
But it's Christmas and
you're allowed nice things

07:45.291 --> 07:46.625
at Christmas.

07:46.709 --> 07:49.625
Well we will see what we can do.

07:50.041 --> 07:51.542
[MUSIC STOPS]

07:52.417 --> 07:55.000
They called
again today.

07:56.792 --> 07:58.959
What this time?

07:59.458 --> 08:03.667
They said they'd like
to get the contract finished

08:03.750 --> 08:07.083
by the end of
the year, they said

08:07.166 --> 08:09.750
it would be a nice treat for us

08:09.834 --> 08:12.417
to have security for Christmas.

08:13.625 --> 08:16.333
Security? Why,
have they tripled the offer?

08:16.417 --> 08:17.375
♪WISTFUL MUSIC FADES IN♪

08:17.458 --> 08:21.000
It's alright
sweetheart, it's alright,

08:21.417 --> 08:23.166
nothing to worry about.

08:23.750 --> 08:26.291
Mince pies
for breakfast Ooh!

08:27.041 --> 08:28.083
[SANDRA AND ANDREW LAUGHS]

08:28.166 --> 08:29.917
[PHONE RINGS]

08:33.375 --> 08:35.667
Pine Falls Holiday Park.

08:35.750 --> 08:38.458
AMBER:
[OVER PHONE]
Hi Andrew this is
Amber from Crumble Cafe.

08:38.542 --> 08:39.291
You wouldn't happen
to have any spare lodges

08:39.375 --> 08:41.750
available tonight would you?

08:42.000 --> 08:44.041
I've a lovely woman
from America here in desperate

08:44.125 --> 08:48.000
need of accommodation because
every room in town is booked.

08:49.041 --> 08:50.959
ANDREW:
Well how many do you want?
I've been empty for weeks.

08:51.208 --> 08:52.458
Oh Fantastic!

08:52.875 --> 08:54.083
[SILENTLY MOUTHING 'please say']

08:54.166 --> 08:56.375
Um not that you've
been empty but, you know...

08:56.458 --> 08:59.333
I know, I know. Well give us
30 minutes to get one warmed up.

08:59.417 --> 09:00.625
Is it just for the night?

09:00.709 --> 09:03.834
AMBER:
For now but, we'll see.

09:09.125 --> 09:14.125
♪QUIRKY MUSIC♪

09:25.792 --> 09:29.792
[MUSIC SPEEDS UP]

09:43.250 --> 09:45.458
Hi, I'm Andrew.

09:45.542 --> 09:46.166
Oh hi, Jessica Bailey.

09:46.250 --> 09:48.083
Oh let me get that.

09:48.166 --> 09:49.834
Oh thank you, it's a
really beautiful place.

09:49.917 --> 09:52.834
Thank you, it's a bit
chilly in there at the moment,

09:52.917 --> 09:54.083
but it will soon warm up.

09:54.166 --> 09:55.333
Great.

09:55.417 --> 09:58.291
[MUSIC STOPS]

10:10.417 --> 10:12.834
Oh wow,
what a cute little lodge,

10:12.917 --> 10:15.166
this is way
better than a hotel room.

10:15.917 --> 10:18.000
Um, have you eaten?

10:18.083 --> 10:19.166
Um Crumble Cafe pie.

10:19.250 --> 10:21.500
Of course, yeah they're
pretty special aren't they?

10:21.583 --> 10:25.500
They're good. Wow I
love this, where did you get it?

10:26.083 --> 10:27.250
Really? You like it?

10:27.333 --> 10:28.208
Yeah, I mean I'm no expert

10:28.291 --> 10:30.500
but I know what
I like and I love that.

10:30.959 --> 10:32.542
Must be a local artist right?

10:32.625 --> 10:34.750
Yeah really local,
you're talking to him.

10:35.959 --> 10:39.041
Yeah I know, I know how
can a big old lump like me paint

10:39.125 --> 10:39.792
something so sensitive right?

10:39.875 --> 10:42.000
No, no, no I
didn't mean that.

10:42.083 --> 10:43.834
[LAUGHS]
It's fine.

10:44.166 --> 10:46.291
Well maybe just a
little. But don't judge me for

10:46.375 --> 10:49.000
judging I'm jet
lagged. I need sleep!

10:49.625 --> 10:53.417
Okay, so, breakfast. Shall
I bring you over something

10:53.500 --> 10:55.000
around what, 8?

10:55.083 --> 10:57.375
That's perfect
Andrew thank you.

10:57.458 --> 11:00.750
♪PLEASANT MUSIC FADES IN♪

11:03.291 --> 11:06.208
Well you have a lovely night
and I'll see you in the morning.

11:06.291 --> 11:07.208
Goodnight.

11:07.291 --> 11:10.125
Goodnight.

11:18.458 --> 11:21.041
She's a singer.

11:21.500 --> 11:22.542
Who?

11:24.083 --> 11:26.625
The guest, Jessica Bailey.

11:27.834 --> 11:30.291
Jessica Bailey is one of the
most sought after Soprano

11:30.375 --> 11:32.458
singers in the US,

11:33.041 --> 11:37.291
her style ranges
from Gospel to Classical.

11:38.500 --> 11:42.166
She's won over 20 major awards!

11:42.250 --> 11:43.792
You Googled her?

11:43.875 --> 11:47.458
I always do. It pays to
know who you have around.

11:47.792 --> 11:50.667
Isn't that what
the internet's for?

11:51.500 --> 11:54.000
I can think of other uses.

11:54.083 --> 11:55.625
I said we'd do breakfast.

11:56.417 --> 12:00.083
We don't do breakfast.

12:00.166 --> 12:00.959
Oh come on, she's in a bind.

12:01.041 --> 12:03.667
Where else is
she going to get food?

12:10.000 --> 12:14.375
Alright. She
liked one of my paintings,

12:17.208 --> 12:21.375
and I liked the
compliment. It's not a crime.

12:22.375 --> 12:26.125
No it isn't Andrew.

12:26.208 --> 12:29.875
It most definitely isn't.

12:30.375 --> 12:34.166
♪GRACEFUL PIANO♪

12:34.250 --> 12:37.625
JESSICA:
Pine Falls is
cozy, cute and warm,

12:39.375 --> 12:41.458
just like the owner.

12:43.083 --> 12:45.083
It's a shame that I
have to leave so quickly.

12:45.750 --> 12:49.000
This is a place that deserves
a couple of days to explore

12:54.542 --> 12:56.500
Oh, I'm sorry but
that's just not good enough.

12:56.583 --> 12:58.458
I have to get to a concert,

12:58.542 --> 13:00.750
a concert that will
not wait for airline problems!

13:01.250 --> 13:02.166
[KNOCK ON DOOR]

13:03.417 --> 13:06.000
Could you call me the second you
get another flight available?

13:06.291 --> 13:10.625
I can't miss that
concert. Ok thank you.

13:13.458 --> 13:14.625
Hi.

13:15.208 --> 13:18.041
There's bacon, sausage,
egg, mushrooms, tomatoes,

13:18.125 --> 13:22.250
preserves, black pudding,
orange juice and coffee.

13:22.333 --> 13:25.083
I thought you'd
prefer coffee over tea,

13:25.166 --> 13:26.709
and I baked some bread.

13:26.792 --> 13:29.834
You've baked, wow!
That's great thank you.

13:30.333 --> 13:31.458
What's black pudding?

13:31.542 --> 13:35.709
Well I'll give you the recipe
if you like it how's that?

13:35.792 --> 13:36.667
Oh okay.

13:36.750 --> 13:39.583
I'm Andrew's
mother by the way, Sandra.

13:39.667 --> 13:43.542
Oh I'm so sorry, I see.
Would you like some coffee?

13:43.625 --> 13:45.250
Or breakfast,
there's kind of a lot.

13:45.333 --> 13:47.750
No, no no thank you,
I don't like to intrude.

13:47.834 --> 13:53.291
I hear
you like his paintings.

13:53.375 --> 13:55.500
Oh I love it,
he's such a talent.

13:55.583 --> 13:59.041
He used to be a full time
artist, you know paintings,

13:59.125 --> 14:00.625
sculpture and pottery.

14:00.709 --> 14:05.750
Really? What happened?
If you don't mind me asking.

14:06.583 --> 14:10.709
Well, I'll just
say he lost his muse

14:10.792 --> 14:13.083
and leave it at that.

14:15.291 --> 14:18.250
Oh, who is she?
She's adorable,

14:18.333 --> 14:19.333
I love those boots.

14:19.417 --> 14:20.083
[LAUGHTER]

14:20.166 --> 14:21.792
That's my grand daughter Katie,

14:21.875 --> 14:27.000
and she's
every bit as cute as she looks.

14:28.792 --> 14:34.709
♪PLEASANT CHIMES AND FLUTES♪

14:44.542 --> 14:46.750
BEN:
Alright Andy?

14:47.458 --> 14:51.000
Oh, morning Ben, I
thought I felt the sun go in.

14:52.625 --> 14:54.250
You go inside love,
get ready for school.

14:54.333 --> 14:58.709
Now no need to be like that
Andy lad. I'm being friendly.

14:59.542 --> 15:01.417
Well you weren't being
so friendly when I wanted to

15:01.500 --> 15:04.542
build a play park, and you
weren't being friendly when I

15:04.625 --> 15:06.625
wanted to build a shop
for my guests to buy food.

15:07.125 --> 15:09.291
You've objected to
everything I've proposed

15:09.375 --> 15:10.792
to try and improve my business.

15:10.875 --> 15:12.375
Well you're best off
selling up then aren't you

15:12.458 --> 15:16.458
Andy lad?
While the getting's good.

15:16.542 --> 15:18.750
This is business Andrew.

15:19.583 --> 15:22.583
Now I know that you've
got an offer on the table,

15:22.667 --> 15:25.166
and if you don't
take it then I can't sell

15:25.250 --> 15:26.291
now we both know that.

15:26.375 --> 15:27.667
Then that's a shame for you.

15:28.333 --> 15:30.125
What and you
think that's it Andy?

15:31.166 --> 15:34.625
A few words on your
driveway and it all goes away?

15:35.333 --> 15:38.583
This is a business opportunity
and I'm a businessman.

15:38.917 --> 15:40.875
My family has worked so hard
to make this place what it is,

15:40.959 --> 15:43.166
and we're not
ready to give it up.

15:43.250 --> 15:47.166
And what is it? Empty buildings!

15:47.250 --> 15:49.333
You can't make this
work without your wife,

15:49.417 --> 15:52.000
a blindman on a
galloping horse can see that.

15:53.500 --> 15:56.792
We'll see. Goodbye Ben.

15:57.750 --> 15:58.667
[BEN SIGHS]

15:58.750 --> 16:01.291
Do the right thing Andy.

16:01.375 --> 16:02.709
At least have a
good Christmas with

16:02.792 --> 16:05.709
what's left of your family.

16:07.583 --> 16:08.208
You know I'm right.

16:08.291 --> 16:11.917
Oi! Get along now Ben Ritchie!

16:12.500 --> 16:13.583
There's nothing for you here.

16:13.667 --> 16:16.333
Oh but there is, Sandra.

16:16.417 --> 16:18.667
Ask your lad
there, he'll tell you.

16:20.208 --> 16:22.875
[BIRDS CHIRP]

16:24.375 --> 16:25.875
I don't want to give up, Mum.

16:26.625 --> 16:28.208
We've worked too
hard and look around.

16:28.291 --> 16:32.333
I want Katie to grow up
here not in an apartment.

16:33.083 --> 16:37.500
Don't get worked up,
he's just a bully love.

16:37.583 --> 16:41.208
Don't give him the satisfaction.

16:51.333 --> 16:56.291
♪GRACEFUL ORCHESTRA SWELLS♪

17:17.000 --> 17:19.125
LENA:
Would you like
me to take one with you in it?

17:19.208 --> 17:22.750
Oh, thank you,
that's really thoughtful.

17:23.125 --> 17:24.959
Smile!

17:40.959 --> 17:45.750
[ORCHESTRAL MUSIC CONTINUES]

17:49.375 --> 17:51.291
JESSICA:
Thank you.

17:52.458 --> 17:56.000
He was a kind of scruffy looking
guy, waxed jacket, curly hair.

17:56.709 --> 17:57.375
Ben Ritchie I'll bet.

17:57.625 --> 17:59.750
What's the deal?

17:59.834 --> 18:02.667
I thought Andrew was a softie
but this guy really got to him.

18:03.041 --> 18:05.917
Ben gets to everyone.
Remember I said this town had

18:06.000 --> 18:07.917
its Dickens characters?

18:08.000 --> 18:11.333
Well Ben would be
two combined, Fagin and Scrooge.

18:11.417 --> 18:12.875
Bah humbug!

18:12.959 --> 18:15.834
♪JOLLY BRASS INSTRUMENTS♪

18:16.542 --> 18:20.000
ADAM:
Good afternoon ladies, and
how are we this fine afternoon?

18:20.083 --> 18:24.166
This is my uncle Adam,
owner and baker extraordinaire.

18:24.250 --> 18:26.458
Ah so you're the
artist responsible for that

18:26.542 --> 18:28.166
heavenly fruit
pie I had last night.

18:28.250 --> 18:31.333
Glad you enjoyed it,
Yorkshire's finest rhubarb

18:31.417 --> 18:34.291
but that crucial pinch
of Seville orange zest

18:34.375 --> 18:36.792
elevates it to the sublime.

18:37.417 --> 18:39.959
I'm sure I recognize you.

18:40.542 --> 18:42.542
AMBER:
Jessica's a singer.

18:43.583 --> 18:46.458
Madison Square Gardens!
Chicago Symphony Orchestra

18:46.542 --> 18:49.542
Movie Magic.
You was the Soprano!

18:49.625 --> 18:52.000
That I was! Wow
you have some memory!

18:52.083 --> 18:54.542
It's only a
couple of years ago.

18:54.625 --> 18:57.417
Five, at least five.

18:57.500 --> 18:58.375
Well, I was
there, and I loved it

18:58.458 --> 19:01.542
and I've never
heard a better Soprano.

19:01.959 --> 19:03.333
I went on
about you that much I thought

19:03.417 --> 19:05.375
the wife was going to
make me sleep on the couch!

19:07.041 --> 19:08.417
Thank you, you
like classical music?

19:08.500 --> 19:11.875
Oh my Gosh! There is never
a moment around uncle Adam

19:11.959 --> 19:14.583
without music. Music or poetry.

19:14.875 --> 19:17.542
Poetry, wow!

19:17.625 --> 19:19.875
Don't let these
baker's hands fool you.

19:19.959 --> 19:21.917
Underneath this
apron beats the heart

19:22.000 --> 19:24.375
of a compassionate romantic.

19:24.792 --> 19:27.750
Speaking of which, we
were just talking about Andrew.

19:28.667 --> 19:31.375
Legend that man!
Heart of gold, and his Mum.

19:31.458 --> 19:32.000
Yeah he
seems really nice.

19:32.083 --> 19:34.041
Oh he's more than nice.

19:34.125 --> 19:36.750
Are you going
back up to his lodge?

19:36.834 --> 19:38.667
I am, I can't get
hold of the airline

19:38.750 --> 19:40.333
about when I fly to Vienna.

19:40.417 --> 19:41.417
For a concert.

19:41.500 --> 19:43.583
Oh I wish I were going to that.

19:43.667 --> 19:45.000
Me too.

19:46.667 --> 19:49.125
Hey, it's not all that
bad, Christmas is coming.

19:49.208 --> 19:51.709
Oh don't say that, I
have to go do my concert and

19:51.792 --> 19:53.250
then get back to
Chicago for Christmas.

19:53.333 --> 19:55.417
Do you have
family in Chicago?

19:55.834 --> 20:00.291
No being a singer,
the road's your home.

20:00.375 --> 20:03.291
kids need their Mom around.

20:03.375 --> 20:05.250
Husband, or boyfriend?

20:05.333 --> 20:05.875
No husbands and
boyfriends kind of need their

20:05.959 --> 20:08.583
partner around too.

20:08.667 --> 20:11.583
Well, why don't you just
spend Christmas here then?

20:11.667 --> 20:13.959
I can't. Because
what I do have is an agent,

20:14.041 --> 20:16.458
who has an awful lot planned
for me over the holidays.

20:16.750 --> 20:19.458
Well, if you have to go
back, let's at least have some

20:19.542 --> 20:20.500
fun while you are here.

20:20.583 --> 20:21.542
Deal.

20:21.625 --> 20:22.834
Okay.

20:22.917 --> 20:25.166
[BRASS INSTRUMENTALS RETURN]

20:27.041 --> 20:27.917
Would you mind
taking these up for them,

20:28.000 --> 20:30.458
the cake's for Katie.

20:30.542 --> 20:31.625
Wow!

20:31.709 --> 20:34.208
♪Jingle bells, jingle bells♪
♪Jingle all the way♪

20:34.834 --> 20:39.583
♪Oh, what fun it is to ride♪
♪In a one horse open sleigh♪

20:39.667 --> 20:41.792
[MUSIC CONTINUES ON RADIO]

20:41.875 --> 20:45.166
Well, we're
waiting on the vegetables.

20:45.250 --> 20:47.792
Thanks for inviting me,
I hope I'm not intruding.

20:47.875 --> 20:49.458
You carried that pie
all the way from town!

20:49.542 --> 20:50.959
You deserve a piece.

20:51.041 --> 20:53.583
And the cake!
I don't mind sharing!

20:53.667 --> 20:55.625
Well, how
magnanimous of you!

20:55.709 --> 20:57.583
Daddy,
are you showing off?

20:57.875 --> 20:59.959
[LAUGHING COLLECTIVELY]

21:01.083 --> 21:02.583
Grandma
said you're a singer.

21:02.667 --> 21:05.083
Oh wow! News travels fast.

21:05.542 --> 21:08.166
Adam recognized me from
a concert I did a few years ago.

21:08.625 --> 21:09.333
I can sing, listen.

21:09.417 --> 21:14.458
♪Silent Night♪
♪Holy Night♪

21:14.542 --> 21:16.917
She's in the
nativity choir at school.

21:17.000 --> 21:21.125
♪Round young virgin♪
♪mother and child♪

21:21.208 --> 21:23.834
That's great Katie,
now try sitting up straight,

21:23.917 --> 21:26.583
take a deep breath, now try
singing from your stomach.

21:26.667 --> 21:29.667
♪Silent Night♪

21:29.750 --> 21:33.291
♪Holy Night♪
Oh yeah!

21:33.375 --> 21:38.333
Katie, well you've
learned something tonight.

21:39.041 --> 21:40.875
What's America like?

21:41.125 --> 21:43.834
Well now. It's a big
big country so there are a lot

21:43.917 --> 21:46.875
of different places but where
I'm from it's nice and warm

21:46.959 --> 21:49.041
in the Summer.
And there's a huge lake.

21:49.125 --> 21:50.959
Is it cold in Winter?

21:51.208 --> 21:53.750
Yes it is. Everybody
wears hats and scarves.

21:53.834 --> 21:55.208
Does it snow at Christmas?

21:55.291 --> 21:57.875
Yes it does. what about
here, you guys get snow at

21:57.959 --> 22:00.041
Christmas right?

22:00.125 --> 22:02.792
No we never
do it's not fair.

22:02.875 --> 22:04.166
Oh that's a shame.

22:04.250 --> 22:05.667
It used to.

22:05.750 --> 22:09.709
When I was young, we
always had a white Christmas.

22:09.792 --> 22:11.625
I bet that was fun
when you were a kid right?

22:12.000 --> 22:13.875
Even when I was
younger it always used to snow

22:13.959 --> 22:15.250
in time for Christmas.

22:16.000 --> 22:17.375
Well maybe it will this year.

22:17.458 --> 22:20.000
Will it? Will yo make
it snow this Christmas?

22:20.667 --> 22:23.667
Katie, Jessica my be
special but she can't control

22:23.750 --> 22:25.083
the weather. Can You?

22:25.166 --> 22:28.875
I wish. I tell you what
though Katie, if i could I would

22:28.959 --> 22:29.959
get you a white Christmas.

22:30.041 --> 22:31.083
Even if I'm not her
to share it with you.

22:31.166 --> 22:33.709
Why won't you be here?

22:33.792 --> 22:35.834
Jessica's a busy lady,
and she has her own family to be

22:35.917 --> 22:37.709
with over Christmas.

22:38.625 --> 22:41.709
Will you help
put up our tree then?

22:42.291 --> 22:44.083
Katie, Jessica's our
guest, she hasn't got any

22:44.166 --> 22:46.542
interest in our Christmas tree.

22:48.709 --> 22:52.917
Oh Jessica if you're
foolish enough to want to be

22:53.000 --> 22:56.208
around this one while she's
on a tree decorating mission

22:56.291 --> 23:01.959
I'd love to. If that's okay?

23:02.041 --> 23:04.792
Yeah that's fine,
I'll get one tomorrow.

23:04.875 --> 23:06.542
Yes!

23:06.625 --> 23:08.917
♪One horse open sleigh♪

23:10.333 --> 23:12.417
♪GRACEFUL PIANO♪

23:13.875 --> 23:15.291
I have to say, the views

23:15.375 --> 23:17.875
in this town are breathtaking.
Everything is like a perfect

23:17.959 --> 23:21.959
patchwork, there are no blocks
of buildings, everything just

23:22.041 --> 23:25.834
seems to fit together. It's kind
of random but it just works.

23:26.250 --> 23:31.333
[CELL PHONE RINGS]

23:33.375 --> 23:34.458
Hello?

23:34.542 --> 23:35.583
AIRLINE:
[OVER THE PHONE]
Ms. Bailey?

23:35.667 --> 23:36.875
Speaking.

23:36.959 --> 23:38.291
AIRLINE:
Oh hello Ms Bailey,
I'm pleased to tell you that

23:38.375 --> 23:40.083
we are now able to
offer you a flight to Vienna.

23:40.166 --> 23:43.083
About time, what date?

23:43.166 --> 23:45.208
AIRLINE:
It will be for
tonight, nine thirty.

23:45.667 --> 23:49.709
Tonight, Oh I'm
sorry I can't make tonight.

23:49.792 --> 23:51.166
I'm too far away I wouldn't-

23:51.250 --> 23:53.291
AIRLINE:
Oh, that may be a
problem. We won't have

23:53.375 --> 23:56.625
anything else for a week or so.

23:59.917 --> 24:01.250
Then that will have to do.

24:02.000 --> 24:02.834
Could you call me when
you've got another date.

24:02.917 --> 24:04.750
AIRLINE:
Okay, I'll see what I can do.

24:04.834 --> 24:06.125
Thank you.

24:10.291 --> 24:13.875
Jessica Bailey what on
earth are you doing?

24:18.041 --> 24:23.959
♪WISTFUL OBOE♪

24:27.166 --> 24:31.542
They are all very
similar, some have more bedrooms

24:31.625 --> 24:35.792
and they are
very well appointed.

24:36.333 --> 24:37.917
And of course
they've got great artwork!

24:38.000 --> 24:39.792
[LAUGHS]

24:39.875 --> 24:42.208
But nowadays,
lodges have to have

24:42.291 --> 24:46.875
flat screen TVs and hot tubs.

24:48.959 --> 24:53.041
And, well, of course we can't
afford to put those things in.

24:53.125 --> 24:55.709
Who goes to a beautiful
lodge in all this amazing

24:55.792 --> 24:57.667
countryside to watch TV?

24:57.750 --> 25:00.667
I sometimes wonder.

25:01.792 --> 25:04.333
I can understand the hot tubs,

25:04.417 --> 25:06.375
I'd like one, myself.

25:06.875 --> 25:09.625
You know in the states,
we go to places like this to get

25:09.709 --> 25:12.667
away from TV and
social media and all that stuff.

25:12.750 --> 25:15.792
We go to
hike and maybe fish the lake.

25:16.208 --> 25:19.083
When I was a kid we used to go
up to sand dunes in Michigan,

25:19.166 --> 25:20.250
I'd swim all day, like,

25:20.333 --> 25:25.083
walk in the woods, barbecue
at night. It was heaven.

25:25.166 --> 25:28.625
[LAUGHS]
You really are a country girl.

25:29.166 --> 25:31.000
Yeah, it's funny,

25:31.083 --> 25:33.250
you get so
caught up in all things

25:33.333 --> 25:35.250
that you think
are important and then...

25:35.333 --> 25:39.583
Then you realize
what really is important.

25:39.667 --> 25:43.792
Now it must
get very lonely of a night

25:43.875 --> 25:47.000
in those five star hotels.

25:47.083 --> 25:48.458
Yeah I know, I have no
reason to complain do I?

25:48.542 --> 25:53.250
No, no I'm serious. You know.

25:53.333 --> 25:56.041
No matter all the wealth

25:56.125 --> 26:00.041
and all the fame
and all the traveling.

26:00.125 --> 26:03.291
But where is home?

26:03.375 --> 26:06.041
Where does your heart live?

26:06.792 --> 26:09.375
When Andrew was traveling for

26:09.458 --> 26:11.291
exhibitions and what-not,

26:11.375 --> 26:15.834
he loved it and he enjoyed being

26:15.917 --> 26:19.291
busy and he loved all the
success, that's what bought

26:19.375 --> 26:22.291
all this to start with.

26:22.375 --> 26:26.875
But, no
matter how much he loved it.

26:27.917 --> 26:30.375
He always wanted to come home,

26:30.458 --> 26:34.000
he always loved to come home.

26:34.083 --> 26:36.291
You know to the fire
and the meal with the family,

26:36.375 --> 26:38.166
and his own bed.

26:38.250 --> 26:40.333
[TRUCK DRIVING UP]

26:41.291 --> 26:42.417
Going my way?

26:42.500 --> 26:44.166
Oh hey!

26:45.083 --> 26:50.000
Gives this one half a chance
and he'll lop down a tree.

26:50.083 --> 26:51.834
I got us a beauty look.

26:51.917 --> 26:54.834
Oh wow! It's going to look so
good, oh and that smell of pine.

26:55.083 --> 26:57.041
Oh if we could bottle that and
sell candles, come on jump in.

26:57.333 --> 26:59.083
Come on love.

26:59.166 --> 27:00.458
Careful.

27:02.333 --> 27:06.458
♪TENSE STRINGS♪

27:12.208 --> 27:15.750
There. Now if you dig
a ten foot radius around that,

27:15.834 --> 27:17.250
that will be good practice.

27:17.333 --> 27:19.125
DON:
Ten foot?

27:19.208 --> 27:20.500
Well near enough.

27:20.583 --> 27:21.375
Don't go too deep,

27:21.458 --> 27:24.208
look just get the hang of it

27:24.291 --> 27:26.458
so as we can get
these new drains dug out.

27:26.834 --> 27:28.333
Can't we just
go on a course?

27:28.417 --> 27:32.333
What? You're on a course,
the Ben Ritchie digger drivers

27:32.417 --> 27:36.166
for beginners! It's easy
enough. Look.

27:39.041 --> 27:41.709
[GRUNTS]

27:43.542 --> 27:45.041
[ENGINE STARTS]

27:45.125 --> 27:47.250
Yeah?

27:49.583 --> 27:52.000
♪JOLLY ORCHESTRA♪

27:52.083 --> 27:53.834
Hot chocolate everyone.

27:53.917 --> 27:54.834
ANDREW:
Oh lovely.

27:54.917 --> 27:56.125
JESSICA:
Oh I just love
trimming the tree.

27:56.208 --> 27:57.500
What shall we start with?

27:57.583 --> 27:58.500
Baubles!

27:58.583 --> 27:59.792
Tinsel!

27:59.875 --> 28:01.959
Oh now we're torn.
[GIGGLES]

28:05.500 --> 28:08.417
Oh that's perfect, I love it.

28:08.500 --> 28:11.208
Oh, good girl!

28:11.500 --> 28:15.000
Here, grab this
and we'll wrap it round.

28:22.500 --> 28:24.333
Is that it?

28:24.417 --> 28:27.166
That's perfect
sweetheart. Uh, Katie. Perfect.

28:28.291 --> 28:31.333
Thanks sweetheart, now
let's put another layer on.

28:32.166 --> 28:33.083
[LAUGHTER]

28:33.166 --> 28:34.291
Oh Katie you're so precious.

28:34.375 --> 28:38.208
Why thank you ma'am. Here, grab
this and lets make a spiral.

28:38.291 --> 28:39.709
Okay.

28:46.083 --> 28:49.583
Hey Katie you know we hang
candy canes on the tree at home.

28:50.125 --> 28:52.583
Grandma do
we have any candy canes?

28:52.667 --> 28:57.709
Candy canes? No love, but
we do have chocolate coins.

28:58.959 --> 29:01.667
Now, Katie, whatever you do,

29:02.667 --> 29:04.875
do not eat these
before Christmas day okay?

29:04.959 --> 29:06.500
Okay.
Do you promise?

29:06.583 --> 29:09.917
I promise.
Because that
would be really naughty

29:10.000 --> 29:11.083
Hey!
What?

29:11.542 --> 29:13.125
You're being naughty!

29:13.208 --> 29:14.542
Oh they're so good
aren't they Jessica?

29:14.625 --> 29:16.125
So naughty.

29:16.208 --> 29:17.417
Do you want to be
naughty as well Grandma?

29:17.500 --> 29:18.125
Me?
Yeah.

29:18.208 --> 29:20.000
Me, naughty
Grandma? Yeah!

29:20.083 --> 29:22.709
No no no no no, yes
alright then okay, here.

29:23.667 --> 29:26.458
Hey! I want to be naughty.

29:26.542 --> 29:29.917
Come on then. Come
on then princess lets all be

29:30.000 --> 29:30.333
just a little bit
naughty shall we?

29:30.417 --> 29:33.417
Oh lovely.

29:33.500 --> 29:34.375
ANDREW:
Oh that's nice.

29:34.458 --> 29:35.166
Hey, why don't
we use this as an idea?

29:35.250 --> 29:37.250
What's that?

29:37.333 --> 29:39.041
Well your Mom and I were
talking about people who come to

29:39.125 --> 29:42.291
these lodges and then watch TV
or play video games when they

29:42.375 --> 29:43.834
should be spending
time with their families.

29:43.917 --> 29:46.667
Well why not turn
a negative into a positive.

29:46.750 --> 29:49.417
Like sure, you can't afford
the upgrades that others can,

29:50.208 --> 29:53.000
so we advertise that the
lodges are deliberately designed

29:53.083 --> 29:54.792
to be retreats
away from all that stuff.

29:55.625 --> 29:57.458
No Andrew it's
okay I understand.

29:57.792 --> 29:59.542
Look.

29:59.625 --> 30:01.000
we can dress
the lodge up in like

30:01.083 --> 30:02.875
a good old
fashioned American style,

30:02.959 --> 30:04.917
photograph it
for a new web site,

30:05.000 --> 30:06.709
I guarantee
you will have guests

30:06.792 --> 30:09.083
looking for a
traditional Christmas retreat.

30:09.458 --> 30:10.625
Let's just
put it out there.

30:14.458 --> 30:16.917
Well um, thanks for
the thought, we'll be okay.

30:17.625 --> 30:19.458
[ELECTRICITY BUZZES OFF]

30:19.542 --> 30:22.750
What, what on
Earths, what's happened?

30:24.125 --> 30:25.250
Oh I shouldn't
have said anything.

30:25.333 --> 30:28.417
No, Katie, would you just
go and get some candles from the

30:28.500 --> 30:29.750
kitchen
cupboard? Thank you love.

30:30.166 --> 30:35.792
No it's alright, I
think your idea is wonderful.

30:37.458 --> 30:41.083
Andrew, well he's a proud man.

30:41.500 --> 30:45.375
He wants to be strong, and
he doesn't like to admit that

30:46.083 --> 30:48.375
he's not a
very good businessman.

30:49.542 --> 30:50.583
I didn't mean to upset him.

30:50.667 --> 30:55.083
No, no no you didn't
love. No he'll come round.

30:55.166 --> 30:57.917
You'll see.

30:59.500 --> 31:03.792
[ELECTRIC WHIRRING]

31:21.500 --> 31:22.959
SANDRA:
Where have you been?

31:25.417 --> 31:28.333
I've got the generator working.

31:28.417 --> 31:30.792
I saw a lot of lights
over by Ben Ritchie's land,

31:30.875 --> 31:33.667
probably the power
company fixing the fault.

31:33.750 --> 31:36.875
anyway the generator should
keep us going until morning.

31:39.709 --> 31:41.625
What?

31:41.709 --> 31:45.709
You know what. You
were very short with Jessica

31:45.792 --> 31:46.917
She's a guest in the park,

31:47.000 --> 31:49.625
lets not burden
her with our problems.

31:49.709 --> 31:53.500
Andrew, I know
you better than anyone.

31:53.583 --> 31:56.750
Mum. Goodnight.

31:57.250 --> 31:59.166
What if today is the day?

32:00.417 --> 32:01.291
What do you mean?

32:01.834 --> 32:05.417
What if today is the day?

32:05.959 --> 32:10.750
Or tomorrow or
next week or next year?

32:10.834 --> 32:13.250
Mum, please just
say what you've got to say

32:13.333 --> 32:14.583
I'm really tired.

32:14.667 --> 32:19.333
One day, you're
going to meet someone.

32:20.125 --> 32:21.875
Who'll
brighten up your world.

32:21.959 --> 32:26.333
Someone
who'll fill you with joy.

32:26.417 --> 32:30.583
Someone to share the good
times and ride out the bad ones.

32:31.041 --> 32:36.667
But you have to
let that person in.

32:38.750 --> 32:40.750
Andrew,

32:42.208 --> 32:45.166
Andrew I know
what you're scared of

32:47.458 --> 32:49.834
but Jessica wants you.

32:50.291 --> 32:54.542
You and Katie.

32:56.291 --> 32:59.041
She was very quick to start
working on the business ideas.

32:59.917 --> 33:04.000
Well that was
from here, not here.

33:04.667 --> 33:09.291
Just give it a chance.

33:09.792 --> 33:12.208
I'm not saying jump straight in

33:12.291 --> 33:15.959
but at least,
give her a chance.

33:16.834 --> 33:19.500
She's going to be gone soon so

33:20.750 --> 33:24.000
We'll see.

33:25.500 --> 33:26.750
♪CONTEMPLATIVE PIANO♪

33:26.834 --> 33:30.291
JESSICA:
It's really not like me,
and I should know better.

33:30.375 --> 33:32.875
All I can put it down to
is the magic of this place,

33:33.417 --> 33:35.792
so
peaceful, so...

33:36.417 --> 33:40.083
Ah! Who
am I kidding,

33:40.166 --> 33:43.208
I'm falling for
Andrew and who wouldn't.

33:43.500 --> 33:45.291
But we live four
thousand miles apart

33:45.375 --> 33:47.500
and he probably hates me now.

33:50.500 --> 33:52.250
I'll call the
airline first thing,

33:52.333 --> 33:54.875
if I can't get a flight
to Vienna, I'll go home.

34:17.667 --> 34:22.250
In the morning you
apologize, it's not hard.

34:33.458 --> 34:36.458
So I left early, hoping
I wouldn't see anyone.

34:36.542 --> 34:37.959
You haven't checked out though?

34:38.041 --> 34:40.000
No I can't, I don't
have anywhere to go.

34:40.083 --> 34:41.834
I could have got a
flight last night but...

34:41.917 --> 34:43.750
What?

34:44.625 --> 34:46.625
There was a flight to
Vienna, last night. But

34:46.709 --> 34:48.625
I promised Katie
I'd help trim the tree...

34:48.709 --> 34:51.750
So you put Andrew and
Katie before your concert?

34:52.583 --> 34:55.500
Yeah, I suppose
I did, how foolish.

34:55.583 --> 34:58.834
No, it's not foolish,
you're a wonderful, warm

34:58.917 --> 35:00.625
thoughtful person.

35:00.709 --> 35:05.667
No I'm not I
just. I don't know.

35:05.750 --> 35:09.083
Listen, when his wife
passed, Andrew had a really

35:09.166 --> 35:12.500
tough time, and of
course his business suffered.

35:12.583 --> 35:14.500
It's never
really recovered.

35:14.583 --> 35:15.750
Oh my goodness,

35:15.834 --> 35:17.333
I know I probably
shouldn't be telling you his

35:17.417 --> 35:20.834
private affairs but everyone
around here already knows.

35:20.917 --> 35:24.500
He can barely even
bring himself to come into town.

35:24.750 --> 35:25.417
Poor Katie as well.

35:25.500 --> 35:26.792
Yeah.

35:27.083 --> 35:29.542
Good morning Jessica Bailey

35:29.625 --> 35:32.041
are we in fine
song this morning?

35:32.125 --> 35:35.959
♪ Sleep my child ♪
♪ and peace attend thee ♪

35:36.041 --> 35:40.000
♪ All through the night ♪

35:40.083 --> 35:41.750
Welsh folk
song, it's not a carol.

35:41.834 --> 35:44.375
♪ Guardian angels... ♪

35:44.458 --> 35:46.125
So you haven't
called the airline yet?

35:47.458 --> 35:48.709
I'm glad.

35:48.792 --> 35:52.041
♪ All through the night. ♪

35:52.667 --> 35:56.458
♪ Soft the drowsy hours are ♪

35:56.542 --> 35:58.917
♪ creeping Hill and vale ♪

35:59.000 --> 36:02.625
♪ in slumber sleeping ♪

36:03.417 --> 36:04.792
Oh I forgot the next bit.

36:05.500 --> 36:07.417
Room for me in the choir then?

36:07.959 --> 36:12.750
♪QUIRKY ORCHESTRA BEGINS♪

36:27.834 --> 36:29.083
ELECTRICAL WORKER:
Mister Hunter?

36:29.166 --> 36:30.083
Mister Hunter?

36:30.166 --> 36:31.375
Can I help you?

36:31.458 --> 36:33.875
I'm from the power company.

36:35.667 --> 36:37.917
We've detected a fault in the
area and I was just wondering,

36:38.000 --> 36:40.417
have you been without any power?

36:40.500 --> 36:42.375
Yes, yes we have. We've
been running on the generator.

36:42.458 --> 36:43.709
I was about to call you lot.

36:43.792 --> 36:46.583
Oh I'm sorry about that, it's a
strange one this one you know.

36:46.667 --> 36:48.792
Our system says that
there's a break in the line,

36:48.875 --> 36:52.917
but there hasn't been any
thunderstorms. I mean the cables

36:53.000 --> 36:56.458
that feed your park
they're all underground as well.

36:56.542 --> 36:58.083
They run across
that area over there.

36:58.166 --> 37:00.750
Yeah I know where they run.

37:01.083 --> 37:02.542
What we'll do is we'll
put you a temporary connection

37:02.625 --> 37:06.125
to the power line, until we
can you know trace and fix the

37:06.208 --> 37:09.417
problem.
But it will take a few hours.

37:10.417 --> 37:13.083
I think I might have
an idea where that is.

37:14.750 --> 37:16.583
♪CONSPICUOUS MUSIC♪

37:25.583 --> 37:26.709
[HEAVY THUD]

37:26.792 --> 37:29.417
[GRUNTS]

37:29.875 --> 37:31.750
Morning, Ben.

37:31.834 --> 37:35.458
I've just been checking.
I've got no power me. Nothing.

37:35.542 --> 37:36.709
Nobody asked
what you were doing.

37:36.792 --> 37:38.083
Is he
the police?
No.

37:38.166 --> 37:41.375
Oi! Get off my land mate!

37:41.458 --> 37:43.583
He's from the power company.

37:52.000 --> 37:53.959
What have you done?

37:54.667 --> 37:56.917
Who me? Nothing.

37:57.000 --> 38:01.083
I found
that like that this morning.

38:01.917 --> 38:04.333
Well you've made a
right mess of it haven't you?

38:08.709 --> 38:10.291
What are you writing?

38:14.917 --> 38:17.792
I'm filling out the details.

38:17.875 --> 38:19.125
Alright.

38:27.917 --> 38:30.041
Why is he doing that?

38:32.583 --> 38:37.333
I've got to send a
report, get this fixed pronto!

38:39.959 --> 38:43.291
Look, uh...

38:43.375 --> 38:47.125
I'm sorry, I never
was any good on that digger.

38:47.625 --> 38:49.667
No worries Ben,
these things happen.

38:51.792 --> 38:55.375
♪CHARMING BELLS♪

38:59.667 --> 39:01.750
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

39:02.667 --> 39:03.750
Hello?

39:04.000 --> 39:06.375
MARVIN:
Don't shout, It's
four in the morning!

39:06.458 --> 39:08.917
Oh hi Marvin, what are
you doing up so late?

39:09.000 --> 39:11.583
Business never
sleeps, am I right Jess?

39:11.667 --> 39:13.083
You're always right.

39:13.166 --> 39:17.083
So you're not in
Vienna, that ship has sailed.

39:17.166 --> 39:19.959
I'm so sorry Marvin.

39:20.041 --> 39:22.667
Not your fault, they're
trying to hit us for some no

39:22.750 --> 39:25.917
show fee but I've
sent them to the airline.

39:26.000 --> 39:27.583
When can I get you back?

39:27.667 --> 39:31.542
Oh um, I don't
know. A few days?

39:31.625 --> 39:34.792
I've got the big one,
Chicago Symphony Chorus

39:34.875 --> 39:38.792
Carnegie Hall. Five nights.

39:38.875 --> 39:40.583
Oh wow! That's fantastic!

39:40.667 --> 39:42.208
That's not the best
of it. I got three solos.

39:42.291 --> 39:45.417
That's amazing
Marvin when is it?

39:45.500 --> 39:49.083
Christmas Eve. So you
got to be back by 22nd

39:49.166 --> 39:52.291
to rest your
voice yada yada!

39:52.375 --> 39:55.166
Oh, so soon.

39:55.250 --> 39:57.125
I didn't realize.

39:57.375 --> 39:59.875
Well, we've got to
make up for the Vienna hit.

40:00.166 --> 40:02.583
Christmas
don't pay for itself, kid.

40:02.667 --> 40:05.625
No, no I
guess it doesn't.

40:05.709 --> 40:07.000
OK well thanks
a million, Marvin.

40:07.083 --> 40:09.208
Hey, where are you going?

40:09.291 --> 40:11.875
I've got a whole bunch of stuff
lined up for Christmas week

40:11.959 --> 40:14.792
we got New Years and
then there's that new theatre

40:16.208 --> 40:17.709
Will you try one of these?

40:17.792 --> 40:20.041
Amber's been on at me for
months to try some American

40:20.125 --> 40:22.583
recipes.
Voila!

40:27.083 --> 40:28.417
[BIRDS CHIRPING]

40:28.500 --> 40:31.291
Katie had a quick whip round
with extra tinsel this morning

40:31.375 --> 40:33.583
before she went to school.

40:33.667 --> 40:35.291
Aw, it looks great.

40:35.375 --> 40:39.959
Ah she loves Christmas, we
try to make it special for her.

40:43.000 --> 40:43.583
Sandra, I hope you don't mind.

40:43.667 --> 40:45.834
And please don't be angry.

40:45.917 --> 40:48.959
But I spoke to Amber
about what happened last night.

40:49.041 --> 40:50.125
Oh.

40:50.208 --> 40:53.583
No, it wasn't gossip I
promise, we kind of bonded

40:53.667 --> 40:54.875
she's really helped me out,

40:54.959 --> 40:56.166
we've become
friends I would never-

40:56.250 --> 41:00.208
It's ok love. I'm used to it.

41:00.291 --> 41:01.875
She told me what
happened to you all.

41:01.959 --> 41:05.792
How bad the
situation is, or was...

41:06.792 --> 41:07.542
I don't know
what it's like now but,

41:07.625 --> 41:10.375
I'd just like
to help if I could.

41:17.375 --> 41:21.375
We have nothing.

41:21.458 --> 41:25.166
We can keep the park
open until the end of January,

41:25.250 --> 41:28.625
then we'll have to close.

41:30.166 --> 41:32.208
There's an offer
from a mining company.

41:34.041 --> 41:39.083
But they will destroy the
park, everyone in town knows it.

41:40.542 --> 41:43.250
That's why Adam was
so quiet about Andrew.

41:43.500 --> 41:49.041
Andrew has a
choice, either he sells,

41:49.125 --> 41:53.917
and we have enough to get a
house and move away from here

41:54.000 --> 41:57.333
and the town
becomes a mining town.

41:58.000 --> 41:59.834
Or we stay.

41:59.917 --> 42:04.625
And I don't really
know how that plays out.

42:07.000 --> 42:09.208
Well I can see why
he doesn't want to sell.

42:09.291 --> 42:12.083
None of us want that.

42:12.166 --> 42:15.500
The thing is,
our piece is very small

42:15.583 --> 42:19.750
compared to
what Ben Ritchie gets.

42:19.834 --> 42:21.375
That was the guy that
was here the other day?

42:21.834 --> 42:25.834
Yes. Our land
sits right between

42:25.917 --> 42:30.750
the access and
Ben Ritche's land.

42:31.041 --> 42:35.500
Now if Andrew
doesn't sell, he can't.

42:38.208 --> 42:40.959
Ah Jessica, morning.

42:41.041 --> 42:42.291
Hello love.

42:42.375 --> 42:44.959
Hi.

42:46.542 --> 42:48.500
Oh right, do
you know I must go.

42:48.583 --> 42:52.500
I've got
some washing I've got to do.

42:57.542 --> 43:00.166
Jessica, um.

43:00.250 --> 43:05.125
I'm...I am...I'm sorry.

43:05.208 --> 43:06.333
No I'm sorry Andrew. I-

43:06.417 --> 43:09.667
Please, um let me explain.

43:09.750 --> 43:13.417
It's been a
difficult time for us,

43:14.583 --> 43:18.458
and I haven't made it any
easier by being overly proud.

43:18.542 --> 43:21.208
I'm a man, I can't
help it sometimes but um...

43:23.333 --> 43:28.041
you were only trying to help
and I should have seen that.

43:29.250 --> 43:31.208
And I'm sorry.

43:34.375 --> 43:38.375
Andrew please let me
help you. And Katie and Sandra.

43:38.917 --> 43:42.375
I don't even know if I can, but
every piece of me wants to try.

43:43.792 --> 43:47.792
I'd love to have
you help us, thank you.

43:49.291 --> 43:50.875
What time does
Katie finish school?

43:50.959 --> 43:52.959
Because we need to go shopping.

43:53.041 --> 43:55.417
♪CHEERY ORCHESTRA SWELLS♪

44:24.834 --> 44:29.583
[CHEERY MUSIC CONTINUES]

44:54.417 --> 44:57.709
[MUSIC GETS CUTER]

45:11.417 --> 45:13.709
[MUSIC FADES]

45:13.792 --> 45:17.291
It's absolutely
perfect except for one thing.

45:17.375 --> 45:19.041
ANDREW:
What's that?

45:19.125 --> 45:20.500
There's
nothing on top of the tree,

45:20.583 --> 45:24.500
it looks unfinished.
Do you have a star, or?

45:25.500 --> 45:27.917
I know.

45:31.583 --> 45:35.333
This is the one
that Daddy made.

45:39.166 --> 45:41.458
Oh that's so amazing!

45:41.542 --> 45:43.083
Daddy made it.

45:43.166 --> 45:44.166
Oh it's beautiful.

45:44.250 --> 45:45.041
ANDREW:
Shall we put it up?

45:45.375 --> 45:48.458
Ready? Two, three.

45:49.417 --> 45:51.959
Aw...
There, lovely.

45:52.041 --> 45:55.875
Andrew, could you make
some more of those please,

45:55.959 --> 45:58.542
I'll have one for
the cafe and one for my flat.

45:58.625 --> 46:01.041
You could
sell those easily.

46:01.125 --> 46:02.208
Really?
Yeah.

46:02.291 --> 46:03.291
Yeah I mean one of those
might even make up for the lack

46:03.375 --> 46:05.291
of snow.

46:05.375 --> 46:06.542
Oh okay.

46:06.625 --> 46:09.250
Alright come on
lets get some pictures.

46:09.333 --> 46:10.250
OK everybody ready?

46:10.542 --> 46:13.750
[CUTE MUSIC RETURNS]

46:17.667 --> 46:19.375
I have to say, I barely
recognize the lodges,

46:19.458 --> 46:21.125
they look amazing!

46:21.417 --> 46:24.291
You're just used to
them, the lodges are amazing.

46:24.375 --> 46:25.625
This is just a sales angle.

46:25.709 --> 46:27.166
I'm going to send
these to my agent,

46:27.250 --> 46:28.875
he can sell anything to anyone,

46:28.959 --> 46:29.625
and then I'll start
work on the web site.

46:29.709 --> 46:32.041
You're a web designer as well?

46:32.125 --> 46:33.250
No, but I'm about to learn.

46:33.333 --> 46:36.583
I can't thank you enough,
all this trouble you've gone to.

46:37.750 --> 46:40.250
It's my pleasure,
I just hope it helps.

46:40.583 --> 46:43.041
I was wondering, you know
as a thank you, if you'd like

46:43.125 --> 46:44.250
to join us at
the Winter Wonder Park?

46:44.333 --> 46:46.458
The what?

46:46.542 --> 46:48.875
Well, since we don't
get any snow any more,

46:48.959 --> 46:51.083
there's this place
and it's got a maze,

46:51.166 --> 46:53.375
woodland walk and a load
of Christmas stuff you know?

46:53.458 --> 46:55.333
Does it have hot chocolate?

46:55.417 --> 46:56.500
Of course.

46:56.583 --> 46:58.583
KATIE:
With marshmallows!

46:58.667 --> 47:00.834
I forgot about you under there.

47:02.208 --> 47:03.500
I'd love to come.

47:03.583 --> 47:05.291
Great, well we're
going to go this Saturday.

47:05.542 --> 47:07.917
The twentieth?

47:08.000 --> 47:11.166
Yeah um, yeah I suppose
it is, you'll still be here?

47:11.250 --> 47:12.500
Yeah.

47:13.041 --> 47:14.417
Of course
she will be here Daddy,

47:14.500 --> 47:17.125
sweetheart's going to
be here for Christmas!

47:21.667 --> 47:24.250
MARVIN:
What, have you bought
shares in the park or something?

47:24.333 --> 47:25.709
No, it's just a fried,
I want to help him out.

47:26.250 --> 47:29.583
I admire your generosity
kid, but they're no friends of

47:29.667 --> 47:32.375
mine and my time ain't free.

47:32.458 --> 47:34.542
Marvin, come on. Just
make a phone call, or two.

47:34.875 --> 47:37.542
I'll make it up to you somehow.

47:37.625 --> 47:42.250
Well. Just for you kid.
Now get back here would ya?

47:46.667 --> 47:48.709
No promises Marv.

47:50.500 --> 47:54.750
♪CONTEMPLATIVE ACOUSTIC♪

48:20.667 --> 48:24.500
♪CHEERY ORCHESTRA♪

48:25.625 --> 48:28.625
BEN:
You'll see evidence
all around Nigel. I'm sure.

48:28.709 --> 48:31.375
I mean, there are
plenty of car tires and feet

48:31.458 --> 48:34.000
that travel
through this whole area

48:34.083 --> 48:36.625
and that's why we
can't be too careful.

48:38.375 --> 48:39.208
What now Ben?

48:39.291 --> 48:43.250
Ah. Gentlemen this
is Mr. Andrew Hunter,

48:43.333 --> 48:45.583
the proprietor of this park.

48:46.041 --> 48:49.000
Gentlemen,
what can I do for you?

48:51.625 --> 48:54.166
DON:
We are...

48:55.750 --> 48:58.583
trusted professionals...

48:58.667 --> 49:02.417
from the forestry commission...

49:03.208 --> 49:05.500
This learned man Ben Ritchie,

49:05.583 --> 49:06.917
Thank you.

49:07.375 --> 49:08.875
Has brought it from...

49:10.417 --> 49:12.333
our attention...

49:14.125 --> 49:16.667
that you're trees are...

49:17.750 --> 49:19.250
Have...

49:20.750 --> 49:23.125
They've got Dothistroma.

49:24.333 --> 49:26.250
Needle blight, Mr Hunter.

49:26.333 --> 49:30.834
And um, we have taken
photos of the infected trees

49:31.458 --> 49:33.667
and it looks like all these
are going to have to come down

49:33.750 --> 49:35.917
to stop the spread.

49:36.000 --> 49:39.083
Shall I go and
get my chainsaw?

49:41.000 --> 49:43.709
This is no laughing
matter I can assure you Andrew.

49:43.792 --> 49:46.417
I mean,
I'm scared about this disease

49:46.500 --> 49:48.208
traveling across the landscape

49:48.291 --> 49:49.875
and decimating my woodland.

49:49.959 --> 49:54.709
I mean What
would Pine Falls look like

49:54.792 --> 49:57.417
without any pines I wonder?

49:57.917 --> 50:01.542
Well I'll wait to get the
letter before I take any action.

50:03.417 --> 50:04.625
The what?

50:04.709 --> 50:06.625
Well surely there will
be a headed letter from the

50:06.709 --> 50:09.792
forestry commission advising me
of the results of the analysis

50:09.875 --> 50:11.542
and an opportunity for me
to discuss my options at an

50:11.625 --> 50:12.583
official meeting.

50:12.667 --> 50:16.208
Yes. Exactly,

50:16.291 --> 50:20.917
and that is
what these men will do.

50:22.500 --> 50:24.291
Or, alternatively, I
could just sell the land to you

50:24.375 --> 50:25.959
now couldn't I,
before there's any trouble?

50:26.041 --> 50:29.917
Well. I might be
prepared to help you solve this

50:30.000 --> 50:33.583
little problem.
However, this land is soiled now

50:33.667 --> 50:35.792
so I will be
dropping my price.

50:35.875 --> 50:37.667
Oh what a surprise.

50:38.333 --> 50:39.667
MR. MOORE:
Andrew Hunter?

50:40.041 --> 50:42.875
Mister Moore,
Threshold Minerals.

50:43.333 --> 50:45.291
Mister Moore we
have nothing to discuss.

50:45.375 --> 50:46.667
Ah you didn't
come and see me.

50:47.417 --> 50:49.291
Mr. Hunter is there somewhere
that we can go and talk?

50:49.375 --> 50:50.875
I'm not here to
pressure you I promise.

50:50.959 --> 50:52.417
You can talk here.

50:54.709 --> 50:55.208
Ow!

50:55.291 --> 50:56.959
This way mister Moore.

50:58.792 --> 51:01.959
What did I say about the
beard? What did I say eh?

51:02.041 --> 51:04.000
His idea.

51:04.458 --> 51:05.417
♪SOFT PIANO♪

51:05.500 --> 51:07.542
Threshold Minerals
deals in facts mr Hunter

51:07.625 --> 51:11.333
and here they are. Whilst your
land holds no significant value

51:11.417 --> 51:13.792
as a mineral resource, in
order to gain access to the land

51:13.875 --> 51:15.375
that does, we
would need to traverse it.

51:16.375 --> 51:19.291
We are prepared to offer you
the same purchase rate as the

51:19.375 --> 51:23.834
resource land. It is a very
generous and, I have to add,

51:23.917 --> 51:27.750
unprecedented offer.

51:33.917 --> 51:35.458
I'm sure it is.

51:36.583 --> 51:39.834
However, if you open a mine,

51:39.917 --> 51:41.250
it will destroy Knaresborough

51:41.333 --> 51:43.291
and the
surrounding areas as we know it.

51:44.375 --> 51:47.041
I also deal in facts.

51:49.709 --> 51:51.625
There is an alternative.

51:52.291 --> 51:55.041
We can circumnavigate
your land Mr Hunter.

51:55.542 --> 51:58.375
It would most certainly
be inconvenient, but not

51:58.458 --> 52:02.750
impossible. Should you decide
that you do not want to sell

52:02.834 --> 52:06.500
to us, your park will inevitably
neighbor the largest potash

52:06.583 --> 52:11.625
mine in the UK, with a steady
flow of large plant traversing

52:11.709 --> 52:15.083
the edge of your
woodland 24 hours per day.

52:22.041 --> 52:25.458
Now that's not a place
that I would choose to holiday.

52:31.625 --> 52:35.208
Take the offer Mr. Hunter.

52:44.625 --> 52:48.583
♪CHEERY ORCHESTRA FADES IN♪

52:55.000 --> 52:56.792
KATIE:
Quick, this way, come on!

52:59.583 --> 53:01.458
Come on, she's off!

53:02.500 --> 53:04.417
♪CHEERY MUSIC SWELLS♪

53:32.000 --> 53:34.917
[MUSIC QUICKENS PACE]

54:01.667 --> 54:02.542
[MUSIC ENDS]

54:02.625 --> 54:05.875
[PHONE RINGS]

54:06.250 --> 54:07.792
Hi Marvin.

54:09.208 --> 54:12.291
Really, that's great!
Could you text me the number?

54:15.792 --> 54:17.875
Um Marv, I'm so sorry,

54:18.166 --> 54:20.375
I don't think I'm going to
get back for the twenty second.

54:21.959 --> 54:26.792
I know, sure,
the twenty third, I'm on it.

54:27.500 --> 54:29.583
Yeah I'll
call the airline and fix it.

54:29.917 --> 54:31.625
No
I can't tonight but I will.

54:31.709 --> 54:34.792
Thanks again for the number
Marvin, I owe you another.

54:37.709 --> 54:38.834
Hey. Oh thank you.

54:38.917 --> 54:40.875
Everything okay?

54:40.959 --> 54:42.917
Sure, it's just my agent.

54:43.000 --> 54:45.166
You're not going back are you?

54:46.917 --> 54:48.625
No, not yet.

54:48.709 --> 54:53.417
Good, because
you're my Christmas present.

55:17.500 --> 55:21.917
♪"12 DAYS OF CHRISTMAS"
ORCHESTRA♪

55:35.000 --> 55:38.208
♪CHRISTMAS JAZZ PIANO♪

55:38.750 --> 55:39.917
There you go.

55:40.000 --> 55:41.917
DAUGHTER:
Excuse me, can you
tell me where you got that

55:42.000 --> 55:45.625
lovely angel from
on the top of your tree?

55:45.709 --> 55:49.542
Sure. Well we have a
local artist who makes a limited

55:49.625 --> 55:52.583
number of them every year.
We believe in supporting local

55:52.667 --> 55:53.750
talent and-

55:53.834 --> 55:56.417
MOTHER:
Oh, local talent yes,
can we have one each.

55:56.750 --> 55:58.291
Sure.

55:58.375 --> 56:01.125
I'd better have a couple
love, if your taking orders.

56:01.208 --> 56:02.500
Okay.

56:02.583 --> 56:04.583
Can we have one
for our house grandma?

56:04.667 --> 56:07.875
Course you can love.
Make that half a dozen love.

56:08.125 --> 56:10.542
I think we could arrange that.

56:10.625 --> 56:14.583
Did I mention
that he also paints?

56:14.667 --> 56:16.083
Oh paintings.

56:16.166 --> 56:17.834
I'll have a look
at them as well love.

56:17.917 --> 56:19.959
Okay.

56:33.709 --> 56:35.291
Thanks.

56:36.041 --> 56:40.458
I think my favorite
thing, were the owls.

56:41.834 --> 56:44.375
My favorite part was
the uh, water fountain.

56:47.375 --> 56:50.917
Oh. yeah, now shall we go
and have a nice, warm bath

56:51.000 --> 56:53.583
uh Katie? Goodnight.

56:53.667 --> 56:56.250
Can we bake
cookies together tomorrow?

56:56.333 --> 56:58.083
Of course, I'm not
sure I'll be any good

56:58.166 --> 57:00.166
but I'll give it a go.

57:00.250 --> 57:02.834
That's okay, my cookies
are the best that grandma has

57:02.917 --> 57:05.750
ever tasted. Lets bake
them in the decorated lodge!

57:06.125 --> 57:08.166
Is that okay?

57:08.250 --> 57:10.709
Yeah, that
sounds like a great idea.

57:13.333 --> 57:14.250
Goodnight Sandra,
thanks for a lovely day.

57:14.333 --> 57:16.667
Night Katie.
Goodnight love.

57:16.750 --> 57:19.625
Come on now, off we go.
Lets get that nice hot bath

57:19.709 --> 57:23.417
eh? Alright,
good girl. Up them stairs.

57:25.875 --> 57:28.041
I'm so glad you came.

57:28.709 --> 57:31.458
Me too, I had a blast.

57:32.750 --> 57:35.083
Maybe you'd like to have a look
around town with me tomorrow?

57:36.041 --> 57:39.125
Around town?
Sure that would be great.

57:40.083 --> 57:42.291
Well I don't go out
much now but they've um.

57:43.166 --> 57:46.375
They've got these lovely little
rowing boats down by the river.

57:46.875 --> 57:47.792
Maybe we could-

57:47.875 --> 57:49.667
I would love to.

57:52.333 --> 57:56.458
Well um, wrap up warm,

57:57.792 --> 58:00.959
it gets um, it
gets cold on the river.

58:01.458 --> 58:03.291
I will.

58:06.959 --> 58:11.667
Andy!
Andy I've been waiting all day.

58:15.709 --> 58:18.041
Great timing Ben, as always.

58:18.125 --> 58:19.125
That bloke who came
round to see you the other day,

58:19.208 --> 58:22.083
from the mining company.

58:22.166 --> 58:25.875
He says he made you a great
offer and you've not answered.

58:26.291 --> 58:27.750
That's correct.

58:28.125 --> 58:29.750
Well?

58:30.750 --> 58:32.291
You have
grandchildren don't you Ben?

58:32.375 --> 58:33.750
Yeah.

58:33.834 --> 58:37.667
Well, did you ever stop
to think what their world might

58:37.750 --> 58:40.333
be like if everybody
sold out their future?

58:40.917 --> 58:43.000
But they'd do well
if we sold all this lot.

58:43.917 --> 58:48.750
Think about it. Your children,
and your grandchildren,

58:48.834 --> 58:49.458
they all live in Knaresborough,

58:49.542 --> 58:50.792
and they have great lives right?

58:50.875 --> 58:54.625
Yeah, worth a hundred
quid a week to live round here.

58:56.542 --> 58:58.750
There won't be an
around here if they build

58:58.834 --> 58:59.750
a huge new mine.

59:01.417 --> 59:05.834
See this town
it just can't accommodate all

59:05.917 --> 59:09.959
that a new mine brings. And if
the town center stays as it is,

59:11.083 --> 59:16.041
the shops, they are going to
get forced out by chains. Then

59:16.125 --> 59:18.542
there'll be retail parks,
housing estates to cope with the

59:18.625 --> 59:24.166
expansion.
It happens every time.

59:26.291 --> 59:29.709
And you can be part of
that, or you can choose to

59:29.792 --> 59:31.375
preserve that life that we have.

59:33.583 --> 59:37.959
Yeah but the offer, I mean
my grand kids could have a field

59:38.041 --> 59:39.000
day with that.

59:39.083 --> 59:40.583
You think so?

59:44.417 --> 59:49.458
Think back, think back to the
happiest times of your life Ben.

59:50.083 --> 59:51.917
Now, tell me about it.

59:54.083 --> 59:57.792
Well, probably um, probably
when I was a kid, round here.

59:59.250 --> 1:00:04.041
we used to build dens and that,
climbing the trees for apples

1:00:04.125 --> 1:00:05.417
and berries all
that kind of stuff you know.

1:00:05.500 --> 1:00:07.834
Yeah those long
Summer days eh?

1:00:07.917 --> 1:00:10.834
Eh, and a good fire in
Winter, messing about in all the

1:00:10.917 --> 1:00:13.583
snow and that. yeah.

1:00:15.417 --> 1:00:17.667
And how much
did those days cost?

1:00:21.417 --> 1:00:25.083
priceless memories Ben.

1:00:29.959 --> 1:00:33.208
Well times change and I want
a good life for those kids in a

1:00:33.291 --> 1:00:35.959
modern world.

1:00:36.041 --> 1:00:38.542
I get it, I do.

1:00:38.625 --> 1:00:43.041
All I'm asking, just have
a think about what I said.

1:00:43.500 --> 1:00:46.583
And see if you'd prefer to have
your grandchildren around you,

1:00:46.667 --> 1:00:48.875
playing on your unspoiled
land, breathing the fresh air.

1:01:08.000 --> 1:01:11.250
♪CHEERY ORCHESTRA RETURNS♪

1:01:16.417 --> 1:01:18.458
Thanks Marvin.

1:01:23.333 --> 1:01:25.125
Oh hi, Mrs. Morgan?

1:01:25.208 --> 1:01:28.083
It's Jessica Bailey
sorry that...

1:01:30.959 --> 1:01:35.542
Oh he did? Really?

1:01:40.041 --> 1:01:42.125
♪GRACEFUL PIANO♪

1:01:42.208 --> 1:01:45.125
JESSICA:
Such a beautiful
day with Andrew and his family,

1:01:45.458 --> 1:01:48.458
I feel so at home with them all.
Tomorrow I'm going into town

1:01:48.542 --> 1:01:51.333
with Andrew, I expect he will
be nervous as, I'm told that he

1:01:51.417 --> 1:01:53.959
has been a little reclusive
since his wife passed even

1:01:54.041 --> 1:01:55.041
though it's been a few years...

1:01:55.375 --> 1:01:57.291
[CALL PHONE RINGING]

1:02:00.291 --> 1:02:01.542
Hello.

1:02:01.625 --> 1:02:03.125
AIRLINE:
Oh Ms Bailey,
we've a flight for tomorrow.

1:02:03.208 --> 1:02:06.959
Tomorrow, no I can't.
Why do you always give me such

1:02:07.041 --> 1:02:08.125
short notice?

1:02:08.208 --> 1:02:10.458
AIRLINE:
Well you said it was
urgent so we've been-

1:02:10.542 --> 1:02:13.000
It is urgent, I just
need a little notice.

1:02:13.083 --> 1:02:15.000
AIRLINE:
Well at this time of
year it can be difficult,

1:02:15.083 --> 1:02:16.125
I've only got
cancellations really.

1:02:16.208 --> 1:02:20.375
Okay listen, book me a
flight for the twenty fourth.

1:02:20.625 --> 1:02:21.834
AIRLINE:
Christmas Eve?

1:02:21.917 --> 1:02:24.041
Yes, Christmas
Eve, to New York.

1:02:24.125 --> 1:02:25.542
AIRLINE:
Well that's going
to be very expensive.

1:02:25.625 --> 1:02:27.500
I don't care about the cost.

1:02:27.959 --> 1:02:28.834
AIRLINE:
Twenty Fourth

1:02:28.917 --> 1:02:30.208
Twenty fourth
of December yes.

1:02:30.291 --> 1:02:31.291
AIRLINE:
Is a night flight okay?

1:02:31.375 --> 1:02:32.583
Night flight's fine.

1:02:32.667 --> 1:02:33.291
AIRLINE:
Okay then
I'll see what I can do.

1:02:33.375 --> 1:02:35.291
Thank you.

1:02:35.375 --> 1:02:37.041
AIRLINE:
Goodbye.
Goodbye.

1:02:41.333 --> 1:02:43.041
What am I doing?

1:02:45.250 --> 1:02:49.625
♪SOFT CONTEMPLATIVE PIANO♪

1:03:07.291 --> 1:03:09.000
Have you ever been
on a rowing boat before?

1:03:09.083 --> 1:03:11.417
No I haven't
especially not in Winter,

1:03:11.500 --> 1:03:14.542
it's delightful.
Look at that beautiful bridge.

1:03:14.834 --> 1:03:17.709
Ah you should
see the in the snow.

1:03:17.792 --> 1:03:22.333
That was built in
1851, and still going strong.

1:03:23.291 --> 1:03:25.250
You love it here don't you?

1:03:25.709 --> 1:03:29.792
Yeah I do, I couldn't imagine
living anywhere else now,

1:03:30.750 --> 1:03:31.625
and I've been around.

1:03:31.709 --> 1:03:32.875
Have you been to America?

1:03:32.959 --> 1:03:37.375
Yeah, I've been to um
New York, um Los Angeles,

1:03:37.458 --> 1:03:39.417
Austin Texas.

1:03:39.500 --> 1:03:41.041
And?

1:03:41.417 --> 1:03:45.208
Well, what I've seen is that
wherever you go in the world,

1:03:45.291 --> 1:03:48.458
what's important
is the people you're with.

1:03:49.333 --> 1:03:53.291
as an artist I was around some
extraordinary people you know.

1:03:54.083 --> 1:03:55.417
But some very
greedy ones as well.

1:03:55.500 --> 1:03:58.709
In Knaresborough
you've got Adam the baker,

1:03:59.208 --> 1:04:01.250
and them you've got
the likes of Ben Ritchie.

1:04:01.667 --> 1:04:05.000
Yeah, I guess that's true.

1:04:05.083 --> 1:04:06.959
I loved my time in
America, it's an amazing

1:04:07.041 --> 1:04:10.792
country, with
some amazing people.

1:04:13.625 --> 1:04:16.250
So, what about
little old England,

1:04:16.333 --> 1:04:17.625
are you enjoying your time here?

1:04:18.500 --> 1:04:21.458
It's an amazing country,
with some amazing people.

1:04:21.542 --> 1:04:23.083
[BOTH LAUGH]

1:04:23.166 --> 1:04:24.458
Are we talking about Adam again?

1:04:24.917 --> 1:04:27.917
No, we're not.

1:04:29.792 --> 1:04:32.875
Andrew Hunter you are
such chivalrous gentleman.

1:04:34.417 --> 1:04:36.709
Would you just kiss me please?

1:04:47.250 --> 1:04:52.166
♪CHEERY ORCHESTRA SWELLS♪

1:05:04.333 --> 1:05:06.291
Can you put in the
vanilla please sweetheart?

1:05:06.375 --> 1:05:09.125
Oh sure, um how much?

1:05:09.208 --> 1:05:10.959
Half a teaspoon please.

1:05:11.500 --> 1:05:14.959
How do I? Of course.

1:05:16.500 --> 1:05:19.291
Don't worry sweetheart,
you'll get the hang of it.

1:05:20.500 --> 1:05:23.166
I guess you can tell that
I've never been a Mom right?

1:05:23.250 --> 1:05:24.750
Well you can be mine now.

1:05:28.417 --> 1:05:30.583
Just for Christmas then.

1:05:31.417 --> 1:05:32.709
Katie you dear thing,

1:05:32.792 --> 1:05:36.625
I wish that, well...

1:05:38.333 --> 1:05:41.792
You're going to stay
sweetheart, you know that.

1:05:43.125 --> 1:05:47.625
Oh Katie, look, I
want let you know that...

1:05:47.709 --> 1:05:51.375
I do love it here
and I love being with you

1:05:51.458 --> 1:05:51.792
and your Grandma.

1:05:51.875 --> 1:05:53.917
And Daddy.

1:05:55.291 --> 1:05:58.041
Yes, of course, daddy too.

1:05:58.125 --> 1:06:00.500
But Katie,
my life is in Chicago,

1:06:01.083 --> 1:06:03.750
I have a house
there, and my work...

1:06:04.750 --> 1:06:06.625
Yes but you can
sing here if you like,

1:06:06.709 --> 1:06:09.750
there's a Christmas choir,
I want to hear you sing...

1:06:11.291 --> 1:06:16.291
Oh Katie. I'm so sorry, I
just want you to be prepared.

1:06:16.792 --> 1:06:18.667
I will have to go soon

1:06:18.750 --> 1:06:19.667
Okay?

1:06:19.750 --> 1:06:21.291
Okay then sweetheart.

1:06:23.458 --> 1:06:25.417
Did you preheat the oven?

1:06:26.750 --> 1:06:29.625
[CELL PHONE RINGING]

1:06:32.458 --> 1:06:33.834
Hello Mrs. Morgan?

1:06:35.208 --> 1:06:37.792
You have orders
for sixteen angels.

1:06:38.458 --> 1:06:39.583
SANDRA:
Sixteen!

1:06:39.667 --> 1:06:42.208
And uncle Adam wondered if
you want to put some of your

1:06:42.291 --> 1:06:44.500
paintings up for sale at the
cafe, I mean I know it's not

1:06:44.583 --> 1:06:46.709
the Louvre but...

1:06:46.792 --> 1:06:47.875
Oh yeah,

1:06:47.959 --> 1:06:52.291
Thank you Amber, this is
great news, you'll be back in

1:06:52.375 --> 1:06:53.917
full swing in no time.

1:06:54.000 --> 1:06:56.625
Thank you so much Amber
and please, thank Adam for me.

1:06:56.709 --> 1:06:57.834
Sure.

1:06:57.917 --> 1:06:59.583
Right well I'd better
get cracking on these Angels if

1:06:59.667 --> 1:07:01.125
they want them
in time for Christmas.

1:07:01.208 --> 1:07:03.125
Andrew!
Andrew are you there?

1:07:03.208 --> 1:07:04.208
Are you okay,
what's the matter?

1:07:04.291 --> 1:07:07.375
Nothing's wrong, I
have great news. I just got a

1:07:07.458 --> 1:07:09.917
call from a distribution buyer
in the US. A woman that supplies

1:07:10.000 --> 1:07:12.917
all the major chains,
they want to work with you!

1:07:13.333 --> 1:07:14.583
They what?

1:07:14.667 --> 1:07:17.250
That Christmas Angel.
They love it! They want to use

1:07:17.333 --> 1:07:19.583
the design and work
with you to create more pieces.

1:07:20.834 --> 1:07:22.917
I, I don't understand.

1:07:23.375 --> 1:07:25.333
You would be doing what
you've always done, being that

1:07:25.417 --> 1:07:28.875
great creative artist, but this
time the world will get to see

1:07:28.959 --> 1:07:29.458
what you can do.

1:07:29.709 --> 1:07:31.041
Who do they supply?

1:07:31.125 --> 1:07:35.375
Who don't they
supply? They're mainstream.

1:07:35.917 --> 1:07:38.667
Andrew, you're
going to do so well.

1:07:39.041 --> 1:07:40.792
But I've got orders
from Amber's customers.

1:07:40.875 --> 1:07:42.875
They want you to keep
painting and designing and doing

1:07:42.959 --> 1:07:45.583
all the things you love.

1:07:46.250 --> 1:07:48.500
They want Andrew Hunter

1:07:48.959 --> 1:07:50.792
the Yorkshire artist
working with them!

1:07:52.208 --> 1:07:54.375
I can't believe it,
I can't take this in.

1:07:54.458 --> 1:07:56.500
This is huge Andrew.

1:07:56.583 --> 1:08:00.291
Does this mean that we
can keep the park open?

1:08:00.875 --> 1:08:01.750
Yes!

1:08:01.834 --> 1:08:04.792
[CRIES OF JOY]

1:08:04.875 --> 1:08:07.625
Easily, that beautiful landscape
that I love so much in my lodge.

1:08:07.709 --> 1:08:08.792
Yeah?

1:08:08.875 --> 1:08:11.208
They want to print it,
and they want to see the rest of

1:08:11.291 --> 1:08:14.166
your collection.
Andrew your worries are over.

1:08:16.083 --> 1:08:20.834
[LAUGHTER AND MORE CRIES OF JOY]

1:08:27.083 --> 1:08:28.208
Yes.

1:08:28.291 --> 1:08:29.542
AIRLINE:
You're booked for
the twenty fourth okay?

1:08:29.625 --> 1:08:30.709
Yes, thank you.

1:08:30.792 --> 1:08:32.333
AIRLINE:
It's going to be an
eight o clock flight

1:08:32.417 --> 1:08:36.750
one way to New York
is that alright? Ms Bailey?

1:08:36.834 --> 1:08:38.000
Yes.

1:08:38.083 --> 1:08:40.542
Great and if you can
just confirm that we can use the

1:08:40.625 --> 1:08:41.792
credit card that's stored.

1:08:41.875 --> 1:08:44.500
Yes I can confirm, you
can use my stored card.

1:09:01.500 --> 1:09:06.417
♪CONTEMPLATIVE PIANO♪

1:09:31.417 --> 1:09:36.291
[MUSIC CONTINUES]

1:10:00.709 --> 1:10:05.834
[MUSIC FADES]

1:10:21.125 --> 1:10:27.041
♪QUIRKY ORCHESTRA FADES IN♪

1:10:28.166 --> 1:10:30.417
TOWN CRIER:
Oyez!

1:10:30.500 --> 1:10:34.250
Oyez!

1:10:34.959 --> 1:10:37.667
Citizens of Knaresborough

1:10:37.750 --> 1:10:41.792
are pleased to welcome
Ms. Jessica Bailey of Chicago

1:10:42.083 --> 1:10:46.208
in the United States of America.

1:10:46.583 --> 1:10:48.917
Oyez Oyez!

1:10:49.000 --> 1:10:52.583
Ms Bailey has to
return to her native country

1:10:52.875 --> 1:10:56.834
but she is to
be thanked for her generous and

1:10:56.917 --> 1:11:00.834
magnanimous behavior
from her friends and beloved

1:11:00.917 --> 1:11:04.041
Knaresborough
citizens the Hunter family.

1:11:05.000 --> 1:11:09.125
Hear now all ye citizens,

1:11:09.625 --> 1:11:14.792
Ms Bailey has a
lifetime of free coffee

1:11:14.875 --> 1:11:17.792
and deserts at the Crumble Cafe.

1:11:17.875 --> 1:11:22.917
Who wish her all the best
for her return to Chicago.

1:11:23.792 --> 1:11:28.166
God save the Queen!

1:11:35.458 --> 1:11:37.625
Come on, lets go get
a decent cup of coffee.

1:11:41.375 --> 1:11:42.959
AMBER:
When are you going back?

1:11:43.041 --> 1:11:45.417
Christmas Eve.

1:11:45.500 --> 1:11:47.875
Oh what a shame.
You're going to miss Christmas.

1:11:47.959 --> 1:11:49.750
I have to, I have a
concert on Christmas Eve.

1:11:49.834 --> 1:11:52.083
I'm going straight from the
airport to the Carnegie Hall.

1:11:52.166 --> 1:11:55.166
Wow! That sounds tight!

1:11:55.250 --> 1:11:58.375
Foolish is what it is, I
don't know what I'm thinking.

1:11:59.834 --> 1:12:01.834
I think we both
know what you're thinking.

1:12:02.792 --> 1:12:07.333
I'm a strong, independent
woman, I have built a career...

1:12:08.041 --> 1:12:10.625
We all want
someone special right?

1:12:10.709 --> 1:12:13.291
I've never needed
anybody.

1:12:14.125 --> 1:12:16.458
And now you do,
aren't you lucky?

1:12:19.834 --> 1:12:22.208
I'm behaving like
a lovesick teenager.

1:12:22.291 --> 1:12:24.709
And it feels good, right?

1:12:24.792 --> 1:12:28.166
Of course. It feels
great but if I miss that

1:12:28.250 --> 1:12:31.250
concert, I can kiss goodbye
to my singing career. There is

1:12:31.333 --> 1:12:33.625
nothing worse than being
unreliable and I already missed

1:12:33.709 --> 1:12:34.709
Vienna!

1:12:34.792 --> 1:12:38.000
That wasn't your fault.
Besides, you'll recover.

1:12:38.083 --> 1:12:39.250
You could say that you were ill.

1:12:39.333 --> 1:12:43.917
But I'm not.
No I have to go.

1:12:44.000 --> 1:12:46.917
Like, this is great.
I have had a wonderful time

1:12:47.000 --> 1:12:48.291
but I have
to go and that's it.

1:12:50.542 --> 1:12:53.750
♪QUIRKY MUSIC SWELLS♪

1:12:54.834 --> 1:12:58.250
Smell the
power of my flour ladies.

1:12:58.333 --> 1:13:02.834
Spiced mincemeat and
Christmas crumble slices.

1:13:02.917 --> 1:13:05.083
Oh Adam you're
pulling out the big guns.

1:13:06.041 --> 1:13:08.667
Oh I hope you don't mind
Jessica, but I've asked the

1:13:08.750 --> 1:13:11.542
choir to save a space for you in
our Christmas Carol service.

1:13:11.625 --> 1:13:14.667
I know it's just
our daft little choir but...

1:13:14.750 --> 1:13:18.792
Eh what's wrong?
It's just a bit of singing.

1:13:18.875 --> 1:13:21.041
Jessica has to
go home on Christmas Eve.

1:13:21.291 --> 1:13:24.291
Oh, oh I see.

1:13:24.375 --> 1:13:27.333
Oh, this is silly
I'm being pathetic.

1:13:27.417 --> 1:13:32.125
No you're not love, I
gave up the finest patisseries

1:13:32.208 --> 1:13:35.291
of France to set up here. I
don't regret it for a second.

1:13:35.375 --> 1:13:36.458
You did?

1:13:36.542 --> 1:13:37.750
Oh aye, I've worked for
the best in the world. But

1:13:37.834 --> 1:13:42.083
people like Andrew Hunter
and his family, they only come

1:13:42.166 --> 1:13:46.792
around once in a lifetime.
People like them combined with

1:13:46.875 --> 1:13:49.250
our beautiful town
and unspoiled countryside...

1:13:49.834 --> 1:13:54.291
Makes up for the lack of
Christmas snow. I only came here

1:13:54.375 --> 1:13:58.500
for a Summer writing
holiday. That was two years ago.

1:13:59.959 --> 1:14:01.125
Oh you're not helping.

1:14:01.208 --> 1:14:06.542
Or maybe we are Jess. Maybe
we are, have a crumble slice.

1:14:11.750 --> 1:14:15.250
♪SOFT FOLKSY FLUTE♪

1:14:25.458 --> 1:14:27.667
Ben! Listen,

1:14:27.750 --> 1:14:30.542
I can't match what
Threshold minerals are offering

1:14:30.625 --> 1:14:33.000
but if you still
want to sell your land

1:14:33.083 --> 1:14:33.875
I'll pay over the market price,

1:14:33.959 --> 1:14:36.125
maybe half of
what they're offering.

1:14:37.375 --> 1:14:38.542
Why?

1:14:38.625 --> 1:14:41.750
Because. I can't live
with myself if I stand by and

1:14:41.834 --> 1:14:45.041
watch all this get ruined.
Knaresborough deserves to stay

1:14:45.125 --> 1:14:47.959
the great town that it
is, for generations to come.

1:14:50.083 --> 1:14:51.333
Can you afford it?

1:14:51.417 --> 1:14:53.959
Not yet but just give
me a couple of months.

1:15:07.834 --> 1:15:08.125
Sandy?

1:15:08.208 --> 1:15:09.417
Yes love.

1:15:09.500 --> 1:15:12.000
There's
something I have to tell you.

1:15:16.375 --> 1:15:19.834
It's alright love, I know.

1:15:21.291 --> 1:15:25.625
I feel terrible, I don't know
how to tell Katie, or Andrew.

1:15:26.834 --> 1:15:27.875
They'll understand.

1:15:29.333 --> 1:15:32.834
And Katie's
young, it's Christmas,

1:15:33.333 --> 1:15:37.333
she'll be excited. Not to
mention all the presents that

1:15:37.417 --> 1:15:38.959
you've bought her.

1:15:39.875 --> 1:15:41.500
And Andrew?

1:15:44.834 --> 1:15:47.875
Oh Jessica I'm glad
you're here, I'd like to ask

1:15:47.959 --> 1:15:51.125
you to stay for Christmas.
I've just been to order a

1:15:51.208 --> 1:15:55.250
goose and...what's wrong.

1:15:57.917 --> 1:16:02.333
Andrew I'm so sorry, I'm
going home on Christmas Eve.

1:16:02.959 --> 1:16:04.375
I have a flight booked.

1:16:06.208 --> 1:16:08.208
